meanings.definition: To surpass in seeing or observing.
meanings.sent1: The eagle outseen all other birds in the sky.
meanings.sent2: She outseen her classmates in finding the hidden treasure.
meanings.sent3: The detective outseen the criminal with his keen eye for detail.
meanings.sent4: Her intuition outseen any logical explanation for the phenomenon.
meanings.sent5: The telescope's magnification outseen anything she had ever witnessed before.

meanings.definition: To have seen or observed something before.
meanings.sent1: Having outseen the movie already, he knew the plot twists.
meanings.sent2: She outseen the rare flower during her previous visit to the botanical garden.
meanings.sent3: The old man claimed to have outseen the construction of the ancient ruins.
meanings.sent4: Her memory outseen any digital record of the event.
meanings.sent5: The explorer outseen the mountain range long before it was discovered by others.
